        "timestamp": 1610513092
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The only possible introduction to monads</p>",
        "id": 222552334,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1610528853
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Damned sight better than listening to a Haskell programmer trying to explain them.</p>",
        "id": 222581820,
        "sender_full_name": "Todd Trimble",
        "timestamp": 1610546047
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Reminds me of the ‘definition’ of <a href=\"https://emorehouse.wescreates.wesleyan.edu/silliness/burrito_monads.pdf\">burritos as monads</a>.</p>",
        "id": 222598401,
        "sender_full_name": "Fawzi Hreiki",
        "timestamp": 1610552112
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Personally, I prefer <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Hegelian+taco\">tacos</a> though.</p>",
        "id": 222599090,
        "sender_full_name": "Fawzi Hreiki",
        "timestamp": 1610552348
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That paper tried to explain monads as being like burritos, so it was a definition of monads as burritos.</p>\n<p>However, I like the idea of a \"definition of burritos as monads\".  Someone who doesn't know Mexican food asks you what's a burrito.  You tell them it's just like a monad.</p>",
        "id": 222614701,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1610558336
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Huh? The paper describes the \"burrito monad\", so it's exactly describing burrito as a case of a monad, not the other way around <span aria-label=\"upside down\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f643\" role=\"img\" title=\"upside down\">:upside_down:</span></p>",
        "id": 222697914,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1610618574
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Though it concludes like this</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>As you can see, burritos are not so hard to understand, once viewed from the proper perspective – namely, that of category theory</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span aria-label=\"laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f606\" role=\"img\" title=\"laughing\">:laughing:</span></p>",
        "id": 222702938,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1610621805
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In category theory all definitions are interchangeable so it’s just a matter of preference</p>",
        "id": 222706258,
        "sender_full_name": "Fawzi Hreiki",
        "timestamp": 1610624082
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Stated another way, In category theory all preferences are interchangeable so it's just a matter of definition.  <span aria-label=\"smirk\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f60f\" role=\"img\" title=\"smirk\">:smirk:</span></p>",
        "id": 222771097,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1610653010
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>All burritos are Kan extensions.</p>",
        "id": 222826783,
        "sender_full_name": "David Michael Roberts",
        "timestamp": 1610695480
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is it category theory or is it word salad?</p>",
